## Decisions and Action Items

### Decisions
* **Charter Revision:** A show-of-hands poll was taken on proceeding with the revised charter text, assuming mDNS-specific updates are clarified as in-scope under the efficiency goals.
  * **Result:** 11 Yes, 0 No, 18 No opinion.
* **Unicast Local Discovery Draft Adoption:** A show-of-hands poll was taken on whether the working group should adopt the Unicast Local Discovery (ULD) individual draft.
  * **Result:** 11 Yes, 0 No, 18 No opinion.

### Action Items
* **Charter Update:** Chairs to update the proposed charter text to explicitly include mDNS within the scope of the efficiency and proxy cooperation work items before submitting it to the AD.
* **`draft-ietf-dnssd-tsr`:** Esko Dijk to update the draft to clarify that probing is not required for TSR updates on existing, defended names. Esko and Ted Lemon to coordinate on adding a checksum/hash of the data to the TSR option to handle replication clock drift.
* **`draft-ietf-dnssd-advertising-proxy`:** Ted Lemon to propose text on the mailing list addressing the hybrid `.local` subdomain conflict resolution approach and to drive the draft forward now that TSR is stable.
* **SRP Hints:** François Michel to investigate alternatives to port 53 packet-size multiplexing, such as defining a minimal DNS-compliant format or using a dedicated port.

